        <definition>MRMESH_API bool MR::EdgeLengthMesh::flipEdge</definition>
        <argsstring>(EdgeId e)</argsstring>
        <name>flipEdge</name>
        <qualifiedname>MR::EdgeLengthMesh::flipEdge</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>EdgeId</type>
          <declname>e</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>given the edge with left and right triangular faces, which form together a quadrangle, rotates the edge counter-clockwise inside the quadrangle; the length of e becomes equal to the length of geodesic line between its new ends on original mesh; does not flip and returns false if the geodesic line does not go fully inside the quadrangle </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
